"&#xa0;\nWritten evidence from Sense About Science (GMC0021)&#xa0;\nExecutive summary: We believe that the \nGeneral Medical Council\n should have a role in ensuring that doctors work\ning on clinical trials or who worked on a clinical trial in the past on any treatment in current use ensures that the clinical trial has been registered and a summary of the findings is publicly available. \n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n“(i) Selective non-publication of unflattering trial data is research misconduct; \n“(ii) Registered medical practitioners who give grounds to believe they h\nave been involved in such conduct should have their fitness to practice assessed by the GMC.” \n \n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nDecember 2013 \n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n"